# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ADAS Vision Workbench — .gitignore
# Keep the repo lean: code + configs + small docs only.
# Large data/outputs live OFF the repo (E:\datasets\driving, E:\adas_outputs).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Python virtual environment (MUST stay on C:, never committed) ---
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# --- Python bytecode / caches ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Model weights (downloaded; large, never commit) ---
*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx
*.engine
*.tflite
*.bin

# --- Datasets & raw driving footage (live on E:\datasets\driving) ---
data/datasets/
*.mp4
*.avi
*.mov
*.mkv
*.webm

# --- Generated outputs (large; real run outputs go to E:\adas_outputs) ---
outputs/
# Exception: a few small, hand-picked demo assets are meant for GitHub
# (a short annotated clip / GIF / screenshots). Commit those explicitly with:
#     git add -f outputs/demo/<file>
# so the README demo can render on GitHub.

# --- OS / editor cruft ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.code-workspace
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini
.DS_Store

# --- Logs / temp ---
*.log
*.tmp
